description:
South of Market: The Musical
Concept by Pat Blute
Book by Pat Blute & Samantha O'Keefe
Music and Lyrics by Tareq Abuissa
Directed by Christopher Goodwin
Choreography by Lila Green
Stage Managed by John Russell
Creative Direction by Elliott C Nathan
Graphic Design by Micael Butial

Cast: Shishir Dash, Nick DeWilde, Alexandra Feldman, Sara Grossman, Varun Gulati, Austin Hammer, Travis Hedge, Jameela Huq, Rob Klein, Michael Kovacs, Crystal Liu, Sydney Lozier, Caleb Lush, Emma Onasch, Jessica Osegueda, Morgan Pate, Jake Saper, Venessa Vaccianna, and Rolfe Winkler

http://www.zspace.org/southofmarket

The tech industry is broken.

But don’t worry. We know just how to fix it.

South of Market: The Musical [v1.0 Alpha] is the musical comedy that’s disrupting the tech industry and answering important questions like:

→ Have we reached peak saturation in the on-demand economy? Is there anything left to demand?
→ Will venture capital money flow forever or will companies dry up like Tahoe?
→ Is this too awkward for a first Bumble date? There’s a bar. So no. And it’s good fodder for conversation after.

Join the Bay Area community for an evening of musical theatre playing on modern tech culture in San Francisco.

Jokes will be A/B tested to improve laugh conversion rate.

Interested in bringing the whole company? E-mail somathemusical@gmail.com for more information.
name: South of Market: The Musical

Join me at the screening ONLY ONE NIGHT in San Francisco (Sept. 20) with Q&A with Director MATT KUGELMAN and stars including BIANCA DEL RIO!!!! Also Coming to VOD and DVD - check WolfeVideo.com and http://www.hurricanebianca.com/ for tickets and more details!

Starring Roy Haylock as Bianca Del Rio, Rachel Dratch, Alan Cumming, RuPaul, Margaret Cho, Willam Belli, Shangela, Alyssa Edwards & Bianca Leigh. 

HURRICANE BIANCA tells the story of a New York teacher who is fired from a small Texan school for being gay, and returns disguised as “Bianca” to wreak revenge on the town.

description:
Welcome to the first show of our second season here at the one and only Circus Center Cabaret! We’re delighted to be back onstage, showcasing the Bay Area’s best talent for your enjoyment.

Our hot House Band, the Roger Glenn Trio, is back this season, classing up the joint with their sweet, sassy sound. And heading up our all-star lineup is our new Cabaret Chanteuse, the doll who's got it all, Madame Leanne Borghesi! Her stupendous voice will knock you back in your seats one minute, then make you misty-eyed the next. With all this, plus the amazing variety of artists that will always surprise and delight you, the Cabaret is truly back in Full Swing!

So come on in, enjoy a cocktail from our bar, and get into the swing of the Circus Center Cabaret!

WHEN
Friday, September 23 and Saturday, September 24 at 8:00 pm

WHERE
Circus Center: 755 Frederick St. San Francisco

HOW MUCH
All Seats Age 21 and Up Only. 2 Drink Minimum.
VIP Table (includes front-row seating for four and one drink ticket per guest) $250
VIP Seating (includes front-row seating and one drink ticket) $75
General Admission (seated at one of our intimate cabaret tables) $35 in advance, $40 at the door
Standing Tables (standing room admission around bar-height tables) $15

BUY TICKETS
circuscenter.org/cabaret
